org.ctoolkit.restapi.client.adaptee

Interface ListExecutorAdaptee<M>

  • Type Parameters:
    M - the concrete type of request's model object to work with
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    RestExecutorAdaptee<M>

    public interface ListExecutorAdaptee<M>
    The adaptee interface to provide execute implementation for REST GET operation to retrieve list of resources on top of concrete type.
    Author:
    Aurel Medvegy

      • prepareList

        Object prepareList(@Nullable
                 Identifier parentKey)
                   throws IOException
        Prepare request instance as a proxy object to execute a remote call for LIST operation.

        parentKey - the unique identifier of the parent resource as an owner of this resource if any

        the new request instance

      • executeList

        List<M> executeList(@Nonnull
                  Object request,
                  @Nullable
                  Map<String,Object> parameters,
                  @Nullable
                  Locale locale,
                  int start,
                  int length)
                    throws IOException
        Provide execute implementation of the list operation.
        Parameters:
        request - the concrete request instance, see prepareList(Identifier)
        parameters - the optional map of parameters, configuration, and credential
        locale - the optional language the client has configured to prefer in results if applicable
        start - the position of the first result, numbered from 0. The negative number means unused.
        length - the maximum number of results to retrieve. The negative number means unused.
        Returns:
        the list of resource instance matching filtering criteria, otherwise returns empty list
        Throws:
        IOException
